o shared the belief that civilized nations should be able to forge a middle path between capitalism and socialism. Hanes's sweeping study permits us not only to weave social progressivism into the modern Japanese historical narrative but also to reconceive it as a truly transnational movement whose impact was felt across the Pacific as well as the Atlantic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEconomistszJapanvBiography. 0aMayorszJapanvBiography. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  acapital.  acapitalism.  acity politics.  aclass.  aeast asia.  afactory production.  ahistory.  aindustrial production.  aindustrial revolution.  ajapan.  ajapanese history.  ajapanese industry.  amarxism.  amayor.  ameiji restoration.  amodern japan.  anation.  anational economy.  aosaka.  apolitical economics.  apolitician.  apolitics.  aprewar japan.  aprogressive politics.  aseki hajime.  asocial change.  asocial economics.  asocial progressivism.  asocial reform.  asocialism.  atextile industry.  atextile mills.  atransnational history.  atransnational movement.  aurbanism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022849840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092683740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520926837423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520926837/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY